00254         #if defined(APOXI_ENABLE_SMS_EXTENDED_DATA)

00263 
00264         MdhExtendedData & operator =(const MdhExtendedData &ext_data) {
00265             // prevent from self assignment
00266             if (&ext_data != this) {
00267                 INT i = 0;
00268                 for(i; i < c_mdh_max_ext_data; i++) {
00269                     val[i] = ext_data.val[i];
00270                 }
00271             }
00272             return (*this);
00273         }
00274 
00275         UINT32 GetExtData() const{
00276             UINT32 data = 0;
00277             INT i = 0;
00278             for(i; i < c_mdh_max_ext_data; i++) {
00279                 data |= val[i] << (8*i);
00280             }
00281             return data;
00282         }
00283 
00284         void SetExtData(UINT32 ext_data) {
00285             INT i = 0;
00286             for(i; i < c_mdh_max_ext_data; i++) {
00287                 val[i] = (UINT8)(ext_data & 0xFF);
00288                 ext_data >>= 8;
00289             }
00290         }
00291 
00292         UINT8 val[c_mdh_max_ext_data];
00293 };

00338         // assignment operator

00340             if(&gors!=this) {
00341                 delete[] m_buffer; 
00342                 m_length = 0; 
00343                 if(! gors.IsEmpty()) {
00344                     m_buffer = new UINT8[gors.m_length];    
00345                     m_length = gors.m_length;
00346                     memcpy(m_buffer,gors.m_buffer,gors.m_length);
00347                 }
00348             }
00349             return *this;
00350         }
00351 
00352         // is the PDU deleted (starting from 0 position) ?
00353         BOOLEAN IsPduDeleted(INT tpdupos) const {
00354             INT bytepos = tpdupos / 8;
00355             if(bytepos<m_length && m_buffer!=0) {
00356                 BitField8 val(m_buffer[bytepos]);
00357                 return val.GetBit(tpdupos % 8);
00358             }
00359             return FALSE;
00360         }
00361 
00362         // is the buffer empty ?
00363         BOOLEAN IsEmpty() const {
00364             return m_buffer==0 || m_length==0;
00365         }

00368         // copys data from buffer into object
00369         void Fill(const UINT8 * buffer, INT bufferlen) {
00370             delete[] m_buffer; 
00371             m_length = 0; 
00372             if(buffer!=0 && bufferlen>0) {
00373                 m_buffer = new UINT8[bufferlen];    
00374                 m_length = bufferlen;
00375                 memcpy(m_buffer,buffer,bufferlen);
00376             }
